CASTING CALL FOR YOUNG ACTOR:
Hello, I am looking for a young female actor (age 5-8) to play the role in a student short film. The longline is : 

Benny and Veronika have secretly been rekindling their ex-marriage. But when their 6-year-old daughter, Ivy, walks in on them kissing, the pair are forced to explain their complicated relationship - revealing tensions theyâ€™ve tried to ignore.

If interested please contact me for more information. 

Email - j.marsh0120241@arts.ac.uk

topComments.text: It would be useful to have information about dates, location and confirmation that you will be arranging for a performance licence where appropriate.

Whether youâ€™re already planning your sweepstakes or you might tolerate the odd match, weâ€™d love to hear from you. We want to capture the general public from all walks of life and approaches to football.

We're looking for **volunteer background performers **for our film, Hair or No Hair, for a dance party scene,** filming March 23 - 25th **in the Mount Pleasant area in Vancouver, BC. *Please note, we may not require all the background performers for full days.*

We strongly encourage a diverse crowd of people to submit, with a highlight on BIPOC folks. This film is Black female led, and the party is inclusive of everyone, and will showcase the Drag and Go-Go dancing scene in Vancouver.

If you are interested, please register via this link by Feb 27th:
[https://forms.gle/A2SDDnwHHe8g7N1MA](https://forms.gle/A2SDDnwHHe8g7N1MA)

**SHORT FILM CASTING CALL - â€œTAKEAWAYSâ€**

**OPEN TO UNION & NON-UNION - VOLUNTEER/UNPAID**

**DIRECTOR:** Jamie Lam

**CATEGORY:** Independent Short Film - UBCP ULB

**CASTING DIRECTOR:** Cathy Huynh

**COMPENSATION:** Volunteer/Unpaid. Food provided on set. Copy of film. IMDB credit.

**FILMING DATES/LOCATION:** March 21-22, 2026 (TBC) / Vancouver, BC

**SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS:** Please email **takeawaysfilm@gmail.com** with the subject heading

**[Your Name - Role Name]** and include your headshot/photo, resume and demo reel (if applicable)

**LOGLINE:** A reluctant young boy working at his familyâ€™s restaurant learns to step up as his father quietly falls apart after his loss.

**ANDY â€” Male, 10-15, Chinese or East Asian-identifying.** Smart but apathetic, Andy is tired of helping out at the family restaurant, much rather preferring to play PC games at home. Even so, he takes after his dad Sam, embodying kindness and warmth when times get tough - LEAD. CANTONESE PROFICIENCY IS A PLUS.

**SAM â€” Male, 40-50, Chinese or East Asian-identifying.** A caring and kind father, Sam owns and operates the family restaurant. His wife left him a year ago, leaving him to take care of Andy and the restaurant by himself. He grapples with being a good father while trying to manage his own grief - LEAD. MUST SPEAK FLUENT CANTONESE.

**FEMALE CUSTOMER â€” Female, 35-45, Chinese or East Asian-identifying.** This female customers a regular at Samâ€™s restaurant. While paying for her food, she praises Andy for being such a well-brought up kid. 2 lines, 1 scene.

**FEMALE CUSTOMERâ€™S DAUGHTER â€” Female, 5-10, Chinese or East Asian-identifying.** This young girl accompanies her mother to the restaurant. No lines, 1 scene.

**LINDA â€” Female, 40-50, Chinese or East Asian-identifying.** Linda is Samâ€™s ex-wife. She is seen happily walking with another man, as Sam watches from his restaurantâ€™s window. No lines, 1 scene.

**YOUNG BOYS â€” Male, 10-15, Open ethnicity.** These young boys wave at Andy while he works at the restaurant. No lines, 1 scene.

Unternehmenskultur pur â€“ Was Mitarbeiter wirklich motiviert 

Dieser Short ist ein Ausschnitt aus unserer Karrideo Image- und Eventfilmproduktion  Inh. Christian WeiÃŸe Interviewreihe mit meiner Frau Sandra WÃ¶tzel vor der Kamera. 

Employee Relations â€“ Warum Beziehungen im Job alles verÃ¤ndern 

Im ersten Teil beantwortet Petra KrauÃŸ, Immobilienmaklerin aus Frankfurt am Main, die Kernfrage: Was liegt Dir an Deiner Arbeit wirklich am Herzen? Ihre Antwort ist Ã¼berraschend klar. Es sind die Menschen, also Beziehungen, die sie seit Jahrzehnten pflegt. Das ist ein Blick auf Arbeit, der weit Ã¼ber Zahlen und AbschlÃ¼sse hinausgeht. 

Was liegt Dir am Herzen â€“ Immobilien trifft Handwerk 

Im zweiten Teil richtet Sandra eine direkte Frage an einen Heizungsbaumonteur aus dem Team von Hans van Bebber. Er kommt in diesem 14 Sekunden Teaser zeitlich nicht mehr zum Antworten, aber genau dadurch bleibt eine offene Schleife stehen: Wie lange arbeitet er schon dort und was ist das SchÃ¶ne an der Arbeit? 

Arbeitsmotivation im echten Leben â€“ Hans van Bebber im Fokus 

Der Clip gehÃ¶rt zu einem Video, in dem verschiedene Mitarbeiter Ã¼ber ihre Erfahrungen bei Hans van Bebber sprechen. Im Mittelpunkt stehen Employee Relations und Unternehmenskultur, also die Frage, wie Zusammenarbeit im Alltag wirklich gelebt wird. Es wird deutlich, wie stark Arbeitsmotivation davon abhÃ¤ngt, ob Beziehungen respektvoll, stabil und langfristig sind. 

Was motiviert Dich im Job mehr, das Ergebnis oder das Miteinander? 

Christian WeiÃŸe aka Karrideo Imagefilm-Produktion

items.text:
CASTING CALL - â€œThe Sins of Our Fatherâ€
Hi everyone! My name is Emma and Iâ€™m the associate producer for the upcoming feature film The Sins of Our Father. We are excited to be starting our casting process! 

Filming will be taking place mid May to early August, every second weekend approximately (tentatively), in the greater Vancouver area. It is a volunteer project (with IMDb credit, copy, and great company). This will be a UBCP ultra low budget feature film. 

If you are interested in being apart of this amazing project please email your demo reel, resume, and the name of the character youâ€™re auditioning for to thesinsofourfatherfilm@gmail.com by March 8th.

Synopsis:

The Sins of Our Father dissects the crumbling legacy of the Montgomery family in a narrative that blends gritty family drama with surreal, lo-fi sci-fi.

The story begins with Clive, a dying pawnshop owner and lifelong hustler who attempts one final con: using a mysterious, memory-altering projector to force a reconciliation with his estranged children. With his twisted understanding of fatherhood, he plans to "overwrite" their trauma to stage one final, perfect memory.

The film unfolds in an exploration of the fallouts with his three children: Maddie, the eldest, paralyzed by the fear of inheriting her fatherâ€™s toxicity; Leland, a debt-ridden filmmaker shooting adult content to survive; and Julian, a recluse who has signed a "deal with the devil" by accepting tuition sponsorship from Cliveâ€™s ruthless rival, Vance.

The plan shatters when Clive misuses the device. As the siblings uncover the truth, their own demons collide with external threatsâ€”including Vance and a gang of "trustafarian" loan sharksâ€”who descend on the family home to seize the mysterious projector.

In a chaotic climax that blurs the line between memory and reality, the siblings must weaponize the device to escape. Ultimately, Clive makes the only selfless choice of his life, resulting in his children finally being free.

May be an image of text that says 'Main MainCast Cast CLIVE 60s, MALE, WHITE Stubborn. Proud. Assertive. A lifelong grifter and owner of Vancouver's S last independent pawnshop. Clive treated fatherhood like a transaction he could negotiate Too proud to apologize for the trauma he inflicted, he views the memory- altering projector not as a sci-fi miracle, but as the ultimate "fix" to reunite his dysfunctional family.'

May be an image of text that says 'Main Cast MADDIE 35, FEMALE, WHITE/BIRACIAL BIRACIAL Analytical. Caring. Avoidant. Clive's eldest daughter whose fear of becoming her father has paralyzed her ability to move forward. Terrified that her "fucked up" lineage makes her unfit for motherhood, she over-analyzes every aspect of her life and avoids her emotions to avoid making irrational mistakes.'

May be a graphic of one or more people and text that says 'Main MainCas Cast Phon LELAND 30, MALE, WHITE WHITE/BIRACIAL BIRACIAL Free-spirited. Lax. Unbothered. Deep in debt to dangerous "trustafarians" Leland, who is director of adult content, is the result of Clive pushing him too hard to succeed in field he wasn't interested in; now, having taken huge risk by pursuing filmmaking he is paralyzed, afraid that his unsuccessful filmmaking career will prove Clive right.'

May be an image of text that says 'Main MainCast Cast JULIAN 24, MALE, WHITE/BIRACIAL Geeky. Sentimental. Quick-witted. The youngest and damaged by the need for Î± father figure A university student with commitment issues and knack for repairing broken electronics. Alienated by Clive, Julian has signed 'deal with the devil," accepting tuition sponsorship from Clive' arch-rival, Vance -a decision that legally binds him to the villain.'

items.summary:
CASTING CALL - â€œThe Sins of Our Fatherâ€
Hi everyone! My name is Emma and Iâ€™m the associate producer for the upcoming feature film The Sins of Our Father. We are excited to be starting our casting process! 

Filming will be taking place mid May to early August, every second weekend approximately (tentatively), in the greater Vancouver area. It is a volunteer project (with IMDb credit, copy, and great company). This will be a UBCP ultra low budget feature film. 

If you are interested in being apart of this amazing project please email your demo reel, resume, and the name of the character youâ€™re auditioning for to thesinsofourfatherfilm@gmail.com by March 8th.

Synopsis:

The Sins of Our Father dissects the crumbling legacy of the Montgomery family in a narrative that blends gritty family drama with surreal, lo-fi sci-fi.

The story begins with Clive, a dying pawnshop owner and lifelong hustler who attempts one final con: using a mysterious, memory-altering projector to force a reconciliation with his estranged children. With his twisted understanding of fatherhood, he plans to "overwrite" their trauma to stage one final, perfect memory.

The film unfolds in an exploration of the fallouts with his three children: Maddie, the eldest, paralyzed by the fear of inheriting her fatherâ€™s toxicity; Leland, a debt-ridden filmmaker shooting adult content to survive; and Julian, a recluse who has signed a "deal with the devil" by accepting tuition sponsorship from Cliveâ€™s ruthless rival, Vance.

The plan shatters when Clive misuses the device. As the siblings uncover the truth, their own demons collide with external threatsâ€”including Vance and a gang of "trustafarian" loan sharksâ€”who descend on the family home to seize the mysterious projector.

In a chaotic climax that blurs the line between memory and reality, the siblings must weaponize the device to escape. Ultimately, Clive makes the only selfless choice of his life, resulting in his children finally being free.

Casting call!!!!
Hey everyone, I'm just about halfway done casting for my upcoming romance film "A Handful of Love and Demons to Hate" based on a novel just published! The roles listed below are what I'm still in need of, so a character you can portray just send it to the email provided and follow the instructions on the flyer. I can't wait to get started soon and I look forward to everyone's submission. This does take place in GA and filming will start sometime in April. I plan to be finished by mid July. This is non paid however you will receive credit so just letting everyone know. To offset not being able to pay those brining my production together, I will be hosting a wrap up event/party for the last day of filming, offering low price novel copies to the cast instead of regular price, and sending you early access of the finished movie product that way you can see it before it comes out. Also you might have to click on the pictures of the roles because they can look blurry/pixelated at first then they clear up

items.text:
Casting Call For Short Film
Genre: Psychological Drama

Logline: A respected working actor appears to have everything, career momentum, a loving family, and control over his life, until subtle cracks reveal he may be performing the very reality he refuses to confront. 

NATHAN (Lead) Male, 30sâ€“40s. Mixed race (Black / White) A respected working actor balancing career and family or so it seems. Nathan is charismatic, steady, and deeply loved by those around him. He moves through the world with quiet confidence and competence. As the story unfolds, cracks begin to show. Beneath his professionalism is a man holding something unresolved and when that emotional weight surfaces, it does so in a raw, intimate way. This role requires an actor capable of subtle internal shifts and a contained but powerful emotional unraveling. The performance lives in the eyes as much as in dialogue. This is a lead role centered on emotional control and gradual unraveling. 

Email thewritecue@gmail.com for more information!

Casting call for â€˜Springlandâ€™ Interactive Event in Warrington - WA3 4AQ.
From the creators of Halloweenville, an immersive event for families, the new Springtime event is being launched at Partridge Lakes from 28th March to 16th April (potential extension) 

We are looking for experienced and friendly actors to join our lovely team, the role is great fun interacting with families embarking along the Springland trail where you will have a part of the story to engage the participants with, along with in character improvisation. 

We are currently looking for various roles: 

Lead character role - Fairytale Princess 

Playing age 18-23

We have various characters in a full suit including full head piece, rabbit, unicorn etc which are non speaking roles, however if you can do a suited impression/accent this would be great. High energy and interaction needed with enthusiastic actions. 

Fairy - playing age 16-22 

Preferably able to sing to create the springtime magic as part of the interaction with customers. 

Mermaid - playing age 16-25

Preferably able to sing too.

Paid Role - PAYE or Freelance payment Â£20.18 per hour to include rolled up holiday pay.

Applications - Please apply via 

[https://springlanduk.co.uk/join-our-cast/](https://springlanduk.co.uk/join-our-cast/)

Picture is from our last event Halloweenville October 2025.

Like many, I wanted Legacy. We got Academy. But Iâ€™ve been surprisingly drawn in. The YA stuff isnâ€™t overwhelming and is told in service to a solid plot for the first season, with a great captain, a compelling crew, a convincing villain, and some interesting cadets. Iâ€™m enjoying this consistently in a way I havenâ€™t with SNW, which, for me, is hit and miss. What I donâ€™t get are â€œfansâ€ gleeful Academy didnâ€™t break into the top ten. Some of it is MAGA politics. Some isnâ€™t. But itâ€™s ugly and has taken on misogynistic, racist, and homophobic tones. Everything I would hope all Star Trek fans reject. There is no place for bigotry on the bridge. Captain Kirk said that, I believe. ðŸ––

items.text:
CASTING CALL!! HENRY'S GHOST - A COVID-19 STORY
# A lonely widower, driven by the aftermath of COVID-19 isolation, attempts to prove to his son the presence of a spirit haunting his flat, whom he quietly believes to be his wife.

Short Film (15 minutes)

DRAMA 

Manchester-based only!

Travel + Catering provided 

Filming Mid-April 

From Director ***Jacob James Ward*** with previous works such as *'Fallowfield' *and *'he lives here'* which are currently on the festival circuit, comes a film experience with foundations deep within the essential worker communities affected by COVID-19. 

CASTING FOR
# ***HENRY STONE ***
## ***45 - 55 YEARS OLD ***
## ***MALE***
## ***ANY ETHNICITY ***

Henry, a veteran bus driver struggling with survivors guilt, lives as a stoic, working class representation of the mismanagement of the COVID era in the UK. While working as a bus driver at the height of COVID, Henry slowly saw the toll the pandemic had on his social infrastructure - losing friends, and eventually, his wife.  Now, years later with little attempt to process his tragic loss, he makes an attempt to fill the void created by his loneliness by slowly falling down the rabbit hole of conspiracy theories and is disillusioned by the prospect of a ghost living in his flat who he believes to be his late wife. In a desperate attempt, he tries to convince it's existence to his son. 

# ***JAMES STONE ***
## ***20 - 25 YEARS OLD ***
## ***MALE ***
## ***ANY ETHNICITY ***

Despite living a life surviving it all, Henry can now only be saved by his lone son - James.

James, burdened by the pressures of university, his job and his father's declining mental state, represents the loss of youth and importance of growing responsibility brought on by COVID for young people. James sorely wants to reconnect with his father and help them both move on from the death of James' mother. James must convince his father to stop looking for the dead and start talking to the living - which is easier said than done. 

# *EXTRAS WANTED!!*
## ***20 - 60 YEARS OLD ***
## ***ANY GENDER ***
## ***ANY ETHNICITY ***

We are seeking extras to portray Henry's co-workers in a key sequence that explores and visualises his grief and survivor's guilt. 

If you're interested in being part of this important scene and enhancing the world that we are building, please get in touch!!

***CREW:***

DIRECTOR - JJ Ward 

PRODUCER - George Grant 

CINEMATOGRAPHER - Jack Gaskell 

EDITOR - Matthew Wadham 

SOUND DESIGNER - Jacob Kelly 

Our entire crew has a powerful personal connection to COVID, with myself (the Director) having been locked down during my formative years between GCSEs and A-LEVELs. Many more of you out there will have your own Covid story and we'd love to hear from you!

If this sounds like something you'd be interested working on, with an experienced crew looking to take this to film festivals and beyond, then please get in touch! We'll be sending over script segments and asking for self tapes at this time, with studio auditions to come later :) 

Short Film (15 minutes)

DRAMA 

Manchester-based only!

Travel + Catering provided 

Filming Mid-April 

SPEAK SOON!

CONTACTS:
* Message me on this account :)
* Email the director: jacobward044@gmail.com
* Email the producer: georgefgrant@icloud.com

JAMES STONE MALE 20-25 YEARS OLD ETHNICITY: ANY JAMES, BURDENED BY THE PRESSURES OF UNIVERSITY, HIS JOB AND HIS FATHER'S MENTAL STATE, REPRESENTS THE LOSS OF YOUTH AND IMPORTANCE OF GROWING RESPONSIBILITY BROUGHT ON BY COVID FOR YOUNG PEOPLE. items.text: Quick question â€” when you get sides and nobody's free to run lines with you, what do you do? I used to record the other character on my phone and play it back but the timing was always terrible lol. Curious what works for everyone else?

topComments.text: I use ColdRead is designed for this and helps act like a reader during self tapes too

When you record the other character... read the lines out loud for it (and maybe in a different tone/voice) and in your mind (silent) for your character... so the timing would line up nicely when you play back that audio and record your scene ðŸ˜€

**LAKE OF THE BROKENHEARTED**

**Genre:** Indie Horror / Psychological Thriller

**Status:** NON-SAG / NON-UNION FEATURE

ðŸ“ **Location:** North Georgia (Blue Ridge / Atlanta area)

ðŸ“† **Shoot Duration:** 18 days (April 2026)

ðŸŽ¥ **Small, focused, professional indie crew**

**ðŸ”¥ PROJECT OVERVIEW**

We are seeking **one highly skilled SFX Makeup / Practical FX Artist** (or a very small team) with a strong creative eye and a **story-driven approach to practical effects**.

This is a **passion-driven independent feature film**, created by filmmakers investing their own resources to bring a dark, atmospheric story to life. Weâ€™re looking for a collaborator who enjoys shaping horror elements through **practical makeup, prosthetics, and blood effects**, while working closely with the director.

**ðŸ©¸ SFX / MAKEUP SCOPE (PRACTICAL)**

**Note:** All **gunshots and impacts will be created in post-production (VFX)**.

The SFX Makeup Artist will be responsible for **aftermath effects only** (wounds, blood, prosthetics).

â€¢ Demonic baby doll face (practical)

â€¢ Maryâ€™s face â€œeatenâ€ by baby (prosthetic / FX)

â€¢ Tom â€” stab wound (hand)

â€¢ Tom â€” knife cut to neck

â€¢ Mary repeatedly stabbing Tom during climax (practical blood & wounds)

â€¢ **Aftermath of gunshot wounds** (blood, entry/exit wounds, body effects)

â€¢ Owl Totem Mask (practical prop / mask)

â€¢ Creature / Entity: **Tatakala** (prosthetic / creature design)

â€¢ General character makeup for cast

**ðŸ’° COMPENSATION**

**Flat Rate:** **$3,000 total (Labor)**
Production will cover all approved materials and fabrication costs separately.

(Estimated 18 days of work including prep + shoot days)

*This is a micro-budget independent production. Lodging and meals are provided during filming.*

**ðŸŽ­ ROLE REQUIRED**

â€¢ **Special Effects / Makeup (SFX) Artist**

**ðŸ“© TO APPLY**

Please send:

â€¢ Portfolio or reel of SFX / prosthetic work

â€¢ Brief note on experience with blood FX and prosthetic makeup

â€¢ Location & availability in April 2026

items.text:
**CASTING CALL â€“ FEATURE FILM: *****FENECH â€“ The Jeff Fenech Story***** (Professional / IMDb-credited actors only)**

We are currently casting **major principal roles** for our feature film ***FENECH***. These roles are substantial, emotionally demanding, and require experienced performers with **professional screen credits and an IMDb page**.

If you are **new to acting**, this is not the intake weâ€™re seeking for these characters â€” we need the very best we can find.

âœ… **To apply:** Please email **fenech@wingmanpictures.com** with:
* **Headshot** (current)
* **Showreel link**
* **IMDb link**
* Any **brief note** on boxing training / physical skills (where relevant)

â—ï¸**Please do not DM/message us. Email submissions only, thanks.**

## ROLES CURRENTLY CASTING
1) JEFF FENECH (Adult / Lead)
* **Sex:** Male
* **Playing Age:** Late teens through 30s (with later-life moments into 50s depending on casting approach)
* **Ethnicity/Look:** Australian with strong Mediterranean/Maltese heritage; compact, explosive athlete; intense eyes; tough, working-class presence
* **Physical:** Ideally around Jeffâ€™s compact build (approx. 5â€™7â€ region is a plus), believable elite fighter movement
* **Character:** The â€œMarrickville Maulerâ€ â€” raw talent forged into a world champion. Charismatic, volatile, fiercely loyal, and driven by pride, love, and survival. Must carry a full feature film with emotional range: triumph, pressure, family fracture, and legacy.
* **Weâ€™re looking for:** A transformative lead performer with real grit, vulnerability, and **credible boxing ability** (or the proven capacity to train to it fast).

2) JEFF FENECH (Teenager)
* **Sex:** Male
* **Playing Age:** 13â€“15
* **Look:** Wiry, sharp-eyed, street-smart kid; smaller frame but coiled energy
* **Character:** Young Jeff before the fame â€” hungry, fearless, and already hardening. Early glimpses of the champion and the trouble-maker in the same body.
* **Weâ€™re looking for:** A young actor with natural intensity, emotional truth, and the ability to hold the screen opposite adults. Boxing or athletics a big plus.

3) JOHNNY LEWIS (Trainer / Mentor / Lead Supporting)
* **Sex:** Male
* **Playing Age:** Late 30s to 50s (story period)
* **Look:** Classic Sydney boxing-trainer energy â€” lean, weathered, grounded, no-nonsense; authority without trying
* **Character:** The man who builds champions. A brutal truth-teller, disciplined, fiercely loyal. He loves through pressure. Heâ€™s a father-figure, drill sergeant, and moral compass â€” but never sentimental.
* **Weâ€™re looking for:** A heavyweight character actor with presence, sharp instincts, and the ability to command a room in stillness.

4) PETER MITREVSKI (Corner Man / Club Fighter / Trusted Lieutenant)
* **Sex:** Male
* **Playing Age:** 30sâ€“40s
* **Look:** Solid boxing-gym credibility; European/Macedonian background welcome; grounded, capable, watchful
* **Character:** Part of Jeffâ€™s inner circle in the trenches â€” the dependable gym soldier. Loyal, practical, always there when it counts.
* **Weâ€™re looking for:** A strong supporting actor who feels authentic in the fight world. Boxing experience is a major advantage.

5) PAUL FENECH (Jeffâ€™s Brother)
* **Sex:** Male
* **Playing Age:** Earlyâ€“mid 20s
* **Look:** Can be charming but carries instability; capable of both vulnerability and menace
* **Character:** Jeffâ€™s brother â€” the family wound. His actions ignite one of the filmâ€™s most confronting storylines. This role demands emotional complexity: shame, chaos, loyalty, and consequence.
* **Weâ€™re looking for:** A fearless actor who can go dark, human, and unpredictable without clichÃ©.

6) HENRY FENECH (Jeffâ€™s Older Brother â€“ Teen Years)
* **Sex:** Male
* **Playing Age:** 16â€“19 (playing 17)
* **Look:** Scrappy, streetwise, trouble-ready; big-brother energy
* **Character:** Older brother in the early years â€” part protector, part instigator. Heâ€™s a mirror of the streets Jeff comes from.
* **Weâ€™re looking for:** A young actor with edge, authenticity, and strong sibling chemistry.

7) DETECTIVE SERGEANT LYLE CARMODY (Police / Antagonistic Pressure)
* **Sex:** Male
* **Playing Age:** 35â€“55
* **Look:** Sharp, controlled, politically aware; can feel â€œreasonableâ€ while applying pressure
* **Character:** The detective handling Paulâ€™s case. Polite on the surface, strategic underneath. Understands media, power, and how to squeeze a moment.
* **Weâ€™re looking for:** A grounded, intelligent actor who can play subtext, status, and menace without theatrics.

8) DON KING (Promoter / Larger-than-life)
* **Sex:** Male
* **Playing Age:** 50sâ€“60s (story period)
* **Look:** Black, iconic hair, flamboyant presence; showman energy; expensive suits, big grin, predator instincts
* **Character:** The circus master. Charms, sells, manipulates â€” always working the cameras, always working the deal.
* **Weâ€™re looking for:** A commanding actor with charisma, timing, and the ability to switch from â€œshowâ€ to â€œsharkâ€ in a breath.

9) MIKE TYSON (Boxing Icon)
* **Sex:** Male
* **Playing Age:** Earlyâ€“mid 20s (story period)
* **Look:** Compact heavyweight build; intense, unpredictable energy; physical intimidation and vulnerability
* **Character:** A force of nature. The film captures the aura â€” not just the legend, but the man: direct, blunt, and strangely honest in moments.
* **Weâ€™re looking for:** A physically imposing actor with real presence and believable fighter movement. Boxing background strongly preferred.

10) KERRY PACKER (Media Titan)
* **Sex:** Male
* **Playing Age:** Late 40sâ€“60s
* **Look:** Big, hulking, immovable; booming voice; â€œowns the roomâ€ energy
* **Character:** Power and money in human form â€” blunt, confident, amused by most people. A kingmaker presence when he enters Jeffâ€™s world.
* **Weâ€™re looking for:** A powerhouse actor with stature, authority, and sharp wit.

If you or your agent represent talent suitable for any of the above, weâ€™d love to see submissions.

**Email:** fenech@wingmanpictures.com
**Subject line format:** `FENECH CASTING â€“ [CHARACTER NAME] â€“ [ACTOR NAME]`

items.text:
Hello Everyone,

My name is Shaun Daly and I currently in early development of producing a brand-new TV show titled â€˜LOCAL TALENTâ€™. Written and to be directed the talented Bethany McGiveron. The show is set in a town in the North West of England, where in a working-class neighbourhood, a brothel disguised as a â€œsaunaâ€ to the public resides. Within this brothel, we follow the group of women who own, manage and work there. All of whom are an array of characters who get along like a chosen family that will do whatever they can for each other. Helping one another to survive in this modern world that they are all struggling to survive in and catch moments of joy that life is meant to bring to them. 

The show is inspired a little by the Channel 4 documentary A Very British Brothel, along with stories and accounts of people who have worked in the industry. Stories and accounts we are still researching into now. The vibe and tone of the show is a drama/comedy like the likes of the UK Shameless and Brassic to name some examples. It is a show about together, positivity, banter amongst what the characters would consider are their chosen family. However, along with that, each character has their own personal conflicts, struggles, secrets and desperation for survival.

Our plan is to create a pitch package for the series, by producing the pilot episode. Looking to be around 45 to an hour maximum. We are currently in pre-production and are looking to film around the North West, anywhere from Wirral, Liverpool, St Helens and further if necessary.

What we are looking for is talented actors and actresses from around the North West who would be interested in playing the roles below. Warning that the show will explore themes of a sexual nature along with themes of survival and togetherness. Characters will be dressing up in sexy attire for clients and be performing suggestive positions, simulated sexual content and light fetish comedy as well. No intention of nudity to be involved.

If youâ€™re comfortable with this, then please see the roles below and email shaundaly2510@gmail.com:

**CHELSEA**

Female, 30s,

Curvy, expressive, intimidating and hilarious. A dominatrix with sharp wit and a soft interior she hides well. Natural scouser who has moved away from her past in Liverpool and has found a home working as the Dominatrix of the brothel. Confident, funny, a strong presence within the Brothel.

**LYDIA**

Female, 30s â€“ 40s.

Main villain of Series 1. Sharp, polished, cold underneath. Controlling, emotionally volatile. Very manipulative. Knows her beauty can seduce and make slaves of those who fall under her spell. Character will be exploring themes of domestic violence.

**SHIRLEY**

Female, late 30s â€“ early 40s.

Body Positive, full figured, curvy, tom boyish character. Short practical hair. Dry humour and fiercely loyal. Childhood best friend of Tammy.

**TAMMY**

Female, late 30s â€“ early 40s.

Body Positive, full figured, voluptuous, bubbly, girly, cheerful. Loyal, excitable, forms a comedic duo with Shirley. Warm and expressive. Can be nervous and frantic.

**BIG LIZ**

Trans masculine or non-binary performer, 40s â€“ 50s.

Large frame, camp, emotional, theatrical. Switching between dramatic monologues and silly vulnerability. Use of masculine & feminine voice. Strong, comedic, like the mother hen of the group. With only the Manger Julie above them. Seen as second in command and protector of everyone who works for the Brothel.

**MARY** (Receptionist)

Female, 20s - 30s.

Receptionist of the Brothel. Organises all the clients, answers phones, sorts the lunches and evening meals, arranges the rotas for everyone working at the Brothel. She is small, gentle-looking, quietly stressed. The admin backbone of the brothel in the neat office that is seen when you walk in.

**ROSALINE**

Female, 30s.

Slim or average build, messy glamour, clearly exhausted. A touring girl whose unravelling emotional state becomes part of the plot. Mainly featured in the Pilot, may be planned to return for later episodes.

**BLOSSOM**

Female, Dark Skin Toned, late 30sâ€“40s.

A Nigerian woman who works for the Brothel. She is elegant, expressive, deeply emotional. Balances trauma, fear, and warmth. She has come from a tough background and has come to the UK for a better life. For her, working at the Brothel is that better life, compared to the life she had back in Nigeria. She is kind and considerate, but still afraid to stand up for herself. Especially when it comes to her stalker Ade.

**ADE**

Male, dark skin tone, 40s - 50s.

Tall, intimidating, deeply unsettling. Stalker presence, threatening. Strong physical presence. Very smug and cocky. To the point of unbearable. 

**DARREN** (Blossom love interest)

Male, 30sâ€“40s.

Short man, sweet, warm, confident but sensitive. Blossoms love interest and the opposite of Ade. Darren is in love with Blossom and is happy just to spend time with her and even wants to embrace her culture and be a part of her life. He is looked down upon and seen as too soft, especially from Ade. But there is more to Darren than meets the eye.

**NIGEL**

Male, late 30sâ€“50s.

Soft, friendly, policeman. Awkward. Very innocent and naÃ¯ve. Stuff that goes on in the brothel could be seen to make him feel uncomfortable. Good hearted individual.

**STEVE (Office Pennington, Policeman)**

Male, late 20sâ€“30s.

Stiff, easily flustered police officer. Easily manipulated. Tries to act all hard and tough when he is just a pawn for a bigger scheme to be revealed later in the series. Entangled with Lydia.

**CASTING CALL â€“ Athletic Male (30s)**
Paid Video Shoot â€“ Non-union

We are casting a confident, fit male in his 30s for a short-form video shoot promoting a carbon fiber insole.

**What Weâ€™re Looking For:**
â€¢ Male, 30s
â€¢ Lean, athletic build with strong muscle tone
â€¢ Comfortable speaking on camera

**Concept:**
The video will be filmed outdoors, waist-up framing. You will be answering a total of 15 questions that appears on screen in an Instagram-style format. The delivery should feel confident, relaxed, and natural â€” not salesy or stiff.

**Sample Question (Audition Required â€“ Question #3):**
â€œCan you use them in everyday shoes?â€ 

**Audition Requirement:**
To apply, please submit a short self-tape of you answering the question above using the provided script in the photo attached. This helps us ensure youâ€™re a strong fit for the tone and delivery style weâ€™re looking for. Please wear a tank top or tight t-shirt so we can see your muscle tone. 

**Location:** TBD
**Shoot Date:** Within the next 2 weeks, weather dependent

**Pay:**
$75 per hour
Minimum 4-hour guarantee

We expect filming to take approximately 2â€“3 hours. Total time will depend largely on line delivery efficiency, as the camera setup will remain fixed once established.

If interested, please send:
â€¢ Headshot or recent photos
â€¢ Short audition video answering Question #3
â€¢ Your availability within the next 2 weeks

Email - ecomfilmworks@gmail.com 
Subject Line - Insoles Casting 

Thank you!

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of text that says 'Video Question 3 "Can you use them in everyday shoes?" Answer: I use these both for workouts and my daily shoes. They' re low- low-profile, so they don' t change the shape of the shoe. They work especially well with classic or narrow shoes. You stay stylish, but your feet are supported all day long. That' honestly one of the biggest advantages.'

LIFE IN RECORD CASTING CALL
Produced by Hidden Valley Entertainment & Black Spark Productions

Written by Jacob Ellis

Directed by Jacob Ellis

Please Send Headshots, Reel, and Resume to Lifeinrecordfilm@gmail.com

Due Date: Friday, February 27th, 8:00PM

Shoot length: 5 days from April 28th - May 3rd

Film Location: Kelowna, BC

Script length: 14 pages

Travel, Accommodations, and Food will be covered

Pay: IMDB credit, Reel footage, Deferred pay as well as residuals. Rate can be negotiated. 

Synopsis: Arthur Erikson led a tumultuous life, and an even more challenging after life. After `arriving in purgatory, Arthur meets Angel, his case manager. Who leads him on a journey to reflect upon actions he took in his life by listening to cassette recordings of his life. Their relationship shifts between arguing to comradery. Leading Arthur to make the decision whether to damn himself to heaven or to hell.

Trigger warnings: Discusses SA, no nudity required nor will it be shown, simply talked about.

Arthur Erikson: Male, Mid 20s - Early 30s. Thinks highly of himself, working in pharmaceutical sales. Wreathed in toxic masculinity, throughout the short his shields break down revealing a more sensitive person. Dressed in business casual, Put together. Will require a scruffy beard and shaving throughout the shoot.

Please Send Headshots, Reel, and Resume to Lifeinrecordfilm@gmail.com

sharedPost.text:
---

ðŸŒ€ðŸŽ¬ðŸŽ¥ðŸŒš Exclusive Acting Workshop â€“ Final Version .version A.

VERY LOW COST: One-on-One Online via Skype

"This course integrates the poetic realism of Tarkovsky, the practical wisdom of Michael Caine, and the transformative techniques of Stanislavski and Method Acting. Designed to deepen your craft, it focuses on authentic emotional connection and powerful storytelling."

ðŸŽ¬ Created by a British Cinematographer/Director with 31 Years of Experience and 32 Features to His Name

ðŸŒ International Experience: Having worked on films worldwide, collaborating with actors and directors, I bring real-world insights from both sides of the camera. This course is designed to give actors a deep understanding of their craft, emphasizing emotional depth and character development.

ðŸŒ IMDb: www.imdb.com/name/nm1806508

ðŸŒ Showreel: https://enkiproductions1.8b.io

---

ðŸ¤” What You Will Learn:

ðŸŒ€ Emotional Range: Master the ability to express a full spectrum of emotions, making your performances more believable and compelling.

ðŸŒ€ Character Development: Create rich, multidimensional characters by exploring their internal world, external actions, and backstory.

ðŸŒ€ Method Acting: Use personal experiences and emotions to deliver raw, authentic performances.

ðŸŒ€ Working with Directors and Crew: Learn how to hit marks, understand shooting ratios, and collaborate with crew members to enhance your performance.

ðŸŒ€ Scene Preparation: Techniques for script interpretation, emotional connection, and performing under pressure.

ðŸŒ€ Industry Standards: How to create a professional showreel and work effectively with casting directors and filmmakers.

---

ðŸŽ¬ Day 1: Moment-to-Moment Acting (Stanislavskiâ€™s Approach)

ðŸ”¹ Breaking a Scene Down: The use of internal visualization and meditation to "become" the character.

Character Exercise: The Hitmanâ€™s First Kill

ðŸ“ Scene: A low-rent hotel room in Manhattan, lit by a dull winterâ€™s midday light. The sad hum of a ceiling fan, distant sirens, muted traffic below. On the bedâ€”a brand-new sniper rifle.

ðŸ”¹ Exercise 1 (Singular Emotion): Enter the room, pick up the gun, examine it, and prepare for the target. Remain fully in character.

ðŸ”¹ Exercise 2 (Multiple Emotional Shifts):

1. Enter slightly out of breath, feeling reliefâ€”"I made it here. No one saw me."

2. The weight of reality sets inâ€”"Am I really about to kill someone?"

3. Mesmerized by the artistry of the gunâ€”draw on memories of seeing/touching weapons.

4. Snapped back to reality by a sirenâ€”trace the feeling of waking from a dream.

5. Decision madeâ€”move to the window, set up the gun, and wait.

ðŸ”¹ Discussion: How do actors like Heath Ledger, Daniel Day-Lewis, and Dustin Hoffman make their characters so real? Insights from my own experiences on set with actors who never broke characterâ€”even during dinner.

Exercise 3 (If Time Allows): The Phone Call

ðŸ“ Scene: Youâ€™ve done something terribleâ€”enough to make the person you love most leave forever. You must convince them to stay.

ðŸŽ­ Goal: Improvise, using pure emotional truth, until the performance is undeniably real.

---

ðŸŽ¬ Day 2: Making Your Character Believable

ðŸ”¹ Understanding the Psyche: Whether playing a killer or an ordinary person, you must know your characterâ€™s mind.

Character Exercise: The Breaking Point

ðŸ“ Scene: A crowded supermarket. A tired voice announces deals over the PA. You feel unseen, unheard, frustratedâ€”until suddenly, youâ€™re holding an AK-47. (Note: These scenes are purely acting exercises. They can be altered if a student is uncomfortable.)

ðŸ”¹ Alternative Scene: A character about to detonate a bomb, written in the style of Heath Ledgerâ€™s Joker.

ðŸ”¹ Alternative Scene: A video call to the person you love mostâ€”telling them why. (Scripted or improv.)

ðŸ“ Final Monologue Exercise: "Hi everyoneâ€¦ Tomorrowâ€™s going to be different." The last words before an irreversible decision.

ðŸ”¹ Accents: Versatility in performanceâ€”working with British, American (Deep South), and Northern Irish accents.

ðŸ”¹ Final Exercise: The Power of Stillnessâ€”sit before the camera, smiling, at total peace. Convey pure serenity.

---

ðŸŽ¬ Day 3: Working with a Director and Crew

ðŸ”¹ Understanding Your Role: How an actor fits into the filmmaking process.

ðŸ”¹ Hitting Marks & Lighting: The technical side of making performances shine.

ðŸ”¹ Shooting Ratios: How they affect your performance.

ðŸ”¹ Crew Collaboration: Understanding continuity, sound, makeup, cinematography, and direction.

Final Showreel Scenes (Day 3):

ðŸŽ­ Sinister: "So you really think you got away with it? You really think that?" (Improv)

ðŸŽ­ Heartbroken: "But I didnâ€™t mean it... please, please, donâ€™t leave meâ€¦" (Improv)

ðŸŽ­ Insane (Joker-like): "Mmm... if E = mcÂ², then time versus chaos... who cares?" (Improv)

ðŸŽ­ Flat & Emotionless: "Weâ€™re born, we live, we die. Thatâ€™s it." (Improv)

ðŸ”¹ Goal: Draw from personal experiences and trace memories to make the performances deeply real.

---

ðŸŽ¬ Day 4: Fear and Survival â€“ Personal Experience & Character Creation

ðŸ”¹ Deep Dive: Exploring fear, survival, and desperation in character work.

Exercise 1: The Jungle Escape

ðŸ“ Scene: Youâ€™re lost in the jungle at night, exhausted, your breath the only sound. Every step is agony, but stopping means death. You call outâ€”pleading for help. No answer.

ðŸŽ­ Emotions to Explore:

1. Fear of death â€“ the realization that no one is coming.

2. Desperation â€“ the raw instinct to survive.

3. Physical exhaustion â€“ feeling your body give in.

ðŸŽ­ Method Process:

1. Internal Visualization â€“ Close your eyes, hear the insects, the rustling leaves, your pounding heartbeat.

2. Personal Connection â€“ Recall a moment when you felt completely lost or afraid.

3. Scene Execution â€“ Let the emotions guide your body and voice.

Exercise 2: The Phone Call Redux

ðŸ“ Scene: Youâ€™re on the phone with a loved one. You need their help. If they refuse, itâ€™s over. What do you say? What do you leave out?

ðŸŽ­ Objective: Make the desperation feel real. This is life or death.

---

Final Performance (Day 4):

Students will perform a final emotional scene, bringing together everything theyâ€™ve learned. These performances will be recorded as raw material for their showreel.

---

ðŸŽ¬ðŸŽ¥ Ready to Elevate Your Acting?

This isnâ€™t just a classâ€”itâ€™s an intense, immersive experience that will change the way you act forever.

ðŸŒ To Enroll: p.m.me or e.mail:

mikeenkiproductions1@gmail.com

Letâ€™s create something unforgettable.

Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with only cheating. Based on a real story.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

âš¡ï¸Need to create your first showreel / freshen up your old one?âš¡ï¸
Happy Sunday all!

I provide a very affordable showreel service for new or established actors/directors/cinematographers/comedians/hobbyists etc.

Basically, send me your footage (or I can try and source it for you online if it's commercially aired) and I shall edit it together into a lovely reel.

Please see samples of recent clients in the link below ðŸ˜Ž

I'm an actor myself so I know how frustrating it can be, especially when you're starting out, to collate your footage together to get more work, without wanting to spend a fortune.

My rates are Â£20/hour, with duration of work depending on how much footage you have. The average reels have been around Â£80-Â£100 for my clients. Much more affordable than the companies that charge Â£250+ !!

items.text:
# **REAP LOVE: SHORT FILM CASTING CALL **
> ***"What would happen if the Grim Reaper falls in love?"***

Hi guys, hope you are all well! 

Currently, I am producing a short film called â€˜Reap Loveâ€™, and we are casting one of our main actors, â€œThe Reaperâ€, for this short film! 

**LOGLINE**: When the Grim Reaper meets a girl in a near-death experience, he must choose between love and his soul-collecting job

**LEAD ROLE** â€œThe Reaperâ€: (Lead, Male, 20-29): Tim Burton-like appearance. Preferably tall around 5'10 - 6'0. This is a non-dialogue role, focused on good control of facial expression. The character is a loner who is emotionally numb, buried in his job and closed off to the world around him. Later, towards the end of the film, he begins to learn to express his emotions through the love he finds unexpectedly (additionally, there is one kiss scene included in this film)

This is a non-dialogue role with the focus in good control with facial and bodily expression

**REQUIRED MEDIA**: Headshot/Photo, Video Reel, Resume

**SHOOT LOCATIONS**: Focused in Farnham & Guildford 

**SHOOT DATES**: Monday 2nd March - Friday 6th March 2026 

**COMPENSATION**: Unpaid, but Travel & Catering will be covered and provided for the shoot week. 

I have linked the Mandy and Backstage casting platforms for anyone interested in the main role: 

**MANDY**: [[https://www.mandy.com/aa/project/3103444/reap-love/?role_id=5469086](https://www.mandy.com/aa/project/3103444/reap-love/?role_id=5469086)](https://www.mandy.com/aa/project/3103444/reap-love/?role_id=5469086)

**BACKSTAGE**: [[https://www.backstage.com/casting/reap-love-3104102/](https://www.backstage.com/casting/reap-love-3104102/)](https://www.backstage.com/casting/reap-love-3104102/)

Please contact me as soon as possible (either by the casting platforms, Facebook platform or via email renee_sugui@hotmail.com) if you are interested or know anyone else who would be interested to be onboard with this film! 

Many thanks !! xx

 LOGLINE: 

After the passing of his separated wife, an estranged father reconnects with his daughter after nearly a decade. The two live in different worlds, the daughter works in corporate, making a name for herself in her industry while the father is near rock bottom. In a desperate attempt to feel closer to her, the father recreates meals that the late mother has made in the past. Each meal recalling a simpler time, with tastes and flavors the daughter had nearly forgotten, slowly reconnecting her to her childhood.

Prima Productions is looking for actors who can portray:

Character: A driven corporate professional carrying emotional distance from her past, slowly rediscovering warmth and nostalgia.
